OL,7,FA woman from Cardiff says she has
OL,8,Ffaced bullying and discrimination in
OL,9,Fthe workplace because of her epilepsy.
OL,11,FKorri James, 27, was first diagnosed
OL,12,Fwith the condition when she was nine,
OL,13,Fafter having a stroke.
OL,15,FIn an interview with ITV News, Korri
OL,16,Fsays she's been told by previous
OL,17,Femployers that her epilepsy "puts
OL,18,Fother staff members at risk", leaving
OL,19,Fher feeling upset and shocked that
OL,20,Fshe could be treated in such a way.
